In [5]:
# check stationarity
# AD fuller test
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
dftest = adfuller(df['roomTemp (deg C)'], autolag = 'AIC')
print('1.ADF = ',dftest[0])
print('2.P-value = ',dftest[1])
print('3.Number of lags =',dftest[2])
print('4.Number of observations used for ADF Regression and critical value calculation : ',dftest[3])
print('5.Critical values : ')
for i , val in dftest[4].items():
    print("\t",i," : ",val)

1.ADF =  -5.698715671732383
2.P-value =  7.765100910890617e-07
3.Number of lags = 30
4.Number of observations used for ADF Regression and critical value calculation :  3843

#acf and pacf to determine the autoregression function lags
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf

plt.figure(figsize=(16,7))
plot_acf(df['roomTemp (deg C)'], ax=plt.gca(), lags=50)
plt.show()

#training the model
from statsmodels.tsa.ar_model import AR
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf
from statsmodels.tsa.api import AR
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error

#train model
ar_model_train = AR(df['roomTemp (deg C)'])
ar_model = ar_model_train.fit(maxlag=10)
